
# Migraine Risk App

This project is a Shiny web application that helps users assess migraine risk based on:
- User profile
- Daily biological factors
- Environmental triggers (weather)

The app calculates a baseline risk score and tracks daily changes.


## Installation

You can install the development version of migrane from [GitHub](https://github.com/Programming-The-Next-Step-2025/migrane_risk) with:

``` r
# install.packages("pak")
pak::pak("Programming-The-Next-Step-2025/migrane_risk")
```

## Example

This is a basic example which shows you how to solve a common problem:

``` r
library(migrane_risk)

```
# Example usage: run the Shiny app
run_app()


